mention.text: An October like November ; August a hundred thousand hours , And all September , A hundred thousand
Antwerp ... In the name of God , How could they do it

Those souls that usually dived Into the dirty caverns of mines ; Who usually hived In whitened hovels ; under ragged poplars ; Who dragged muddy shovels , over the grassy mud , Lumbering to work over the greasy sods ... Those men there , with the appearance of clods
no wind that would fan them To a tune
Only this uncomely man with a smoking gun
the gloom ... What the devil will he gain by it
the swift outpouring of the blood
this Belgian man in his ugly tunic
the white-limbed heroes of Hellas ride by upon their horses Forever through our brains
The heroes of Cressy ride by upon their stallions ; And battalions and battalions and battalions -- The Old Guard , the Young Guard
the men of Minden and of Waterloo
the gray coat , and the large hat
the way of it , The way of beauty
the highest word you can find to say of it
A great crowd , all black that hardly whispers aloud .
a dead woman -- a dead mother
the lost who lie dead in trench and barrier and foss
the lost that shall never leave the dock
the lost that shall never again come by the train To the
